1
00:00:37,780 --> 00:00:44,070
♬ I want to go next to you ♬

2
00:00:44,070 --> 00:00:46,490
♬ who are sad ♬

3
00:00:48,250 --> 00:00:54,170
♬ Even if your heart is nothing but scars ♬

4
00:00:54,170 --> 00:00:56,930
♬ I want to have it  ♬

5
00:00:56,930 --> 00:01:01,950
♬ Love Is Blind, Love Is Crying ♬

6
00:01:01,950 --> 00:01:07,110
♫ Love Is Blue, Though you may not know ♫

7
00:01:07,110 --> 00:01:12,010
♬ Love Is Pain, Love Is Lie ♬

8
00:01:12,010 --> 00:01:15,240
♬ Love Is Cold ♬

9
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:23,720
Why are we shopping in the morning? I'm tired.

10
00:01:23,720 --> 00:01:24,890
I feel a bit depressed.

11
00:01:24,890 --> 00:01:27,550
Why? Is the director bullying you?

12
00:01:27,550 --> 00:01:30,380
Is he abusing you like Cinderella?

13
00:01:30,380 --> 00:01:32,780
No way, there's no way.

14
00:01:32,780 --> 00:01:34,700
Whatever he tells you to do, it'll come back like a boomerang

15
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:38,360
and he'll be startled to find himself doing it.

16
00:01:38,360 --> 00:01:41,490
You have that kind of talent.

17
00:01:46,900 --> 00:01:49,940
When will my memory come back?

18
00:01:49,940 --> 00:01:52,760
What do you think my job was?

19
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:55,980
All of a sudden, I felt like going to work today.

20
00:01:55,980 --> 00:01:58,830
You feel left out, all by yourself,

21
00:01:58,830 --> 00:02:01,100
when the rest of the world is carrying on busily?

22
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:04,930
You feel a sense of loss when you see those skyscrapers, endless offices, all those desks,

23
00:02:04,930 --> 00:02:08,810
and there is no place for you, right?

24
00:02:08,810 --> 00:02:10,960
I want to be a part of them no matter what.

25
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:14,370
That kind of desire, urge creeps up on you.

26
00:02:14,370 --> 00:02:16,000
Hyeong, have you been inside my head?

27
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,390
- Who am I?
- Employment preparer.

28
00:02:17,390 --> 00:02:18,790
- Who?
- Employment preparer!

29
00:02:18,790 --> 00:02:20,330
That's right!

30
00:02:20,330 --> 00:02:24,780
The job of an employment preparer is not only studying but also meditating.

31
00:02:24,780 --> 00:02:29,500
The longer you study, the deeper your thoughts grow.

32
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:33,470
Dude, you're becoming more and more human.

33
00:02:33,470 --> 00:02:37,200
Of course you have a long way to go to get to my level.

34
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:39,570
Let's buy stuff, let's finish shopping,

35
00:02:39,570 --> 00:02:41,860
and let's find Bok Nam.

36
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:49,280
I've started wanting to become a better person.

37
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:53,060
Then I'll tell her.
[Episode 8 - Be My Baby]

38
00:02:53,060 --> 00:02:54,890
Let's go together!

39
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:58,700
Bok Sil moved in with the director.

40
00:02:58,700 --> 00:03:00,230
What?

41
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:06,270
Any way that I look at it, the director

42
00:03:06,270 --> 00:03:08,320
100% likes Bok Sil.

43
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:13,760
If that wasn't the case, why would he take Bok Sil and have her charge into his own house?

44
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:17,650
Ah, there is this boy named Louis whom Bok Sil is taking care of for the time being.

45
00:03:17,650 --> 00:03:20,830
He's really nice, but he's... he's...

46
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:27,330
he's weird, he's like an alien. Anyhow, he's a burden.

47
00:03:27,330 --> 00:03:29,620
- I see.
- Yes.

48
00:03:29,620 --> 00:03:34,540
You came all the way here and couldn't meet Bok Sil, what to do?

49
00:03:34,540 --> 00:03:40,630
That's okay. I just came here because I was worried about Bok Sil, as her boss.

50
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:48,360
I know it's not appropriate to say these things when we just met,

51
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:51,670
but both your face and body, no, no...

52
00:03:51,670 --> 00:03:55,810
I mean your heart... Both of them are silky nice.

53
00:03:56,590 --> 00:03:58,030
It's nothing.

54
00:03:58,030 --> 00:04:03,460
Oh, don't do that. You're too perfect.

55
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:16,960
Dad. Louis is living at the headquarters director's house right now.

56
00:04:16,960 --> 00:04:17,990
What did you say?

57
00:04:17,990 --> 00:04:20,440
Ah, it's so annoying!

58
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:24,760
Go Bok Sil is living with them too! I'm going to make them move out immediately.

59
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:28,170
Ma Ri. Ma Ri. Don't get agitated.

60
00:04:28,170 --> 00:04:32,930
Dad will take care of everything, so just don't do anything. Understand?

61
00:04:51,370 --> 00:04:54,160
Who is it at this late hour?

62
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,840
It's past 11 P.M.

63
00:05:05,730 --> 00:05:07,160
President Baek?

64
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:09,190
Excuse me? The president?

65
00:05:10,870 --> 00:05:13,790
Why would Bok Sil's workplace's president come here?

66
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:19,290
Hide in the study for now. Quick!

67
00:05:19,290 --> 00:05:22,500
Ah. The shoes.

68
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:24,660
Hurry.

69
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,900
- Hold this.
- President.

70
00:05:30,900 --> 00:05:33,290
What brings you here so suddenly?

71
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:40,260
Sorry for coming so late. I had to talk to you about something urgent.

72
00:05:40,260 --> 00:05:41,500
Let's go in and talk.

73
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:43,040
Wait a mo—

74
00:05:47,910 --> 00:05:50,210
Is the Director in a high position at work? The president personally comes to talk—

75
00:05:50,210 --> 00:05:52,160
Be quiet!

76
00:05:56,550 --> 00:05:58,930
Is there someone home?

77
00:05:58,930 --> 00:06:02,940
No way. You know full well that I live alone.

78
00:06:07,050 --> 00:06:08,670
I think someone is in that room.

79
00:06:08,670 --> 00:06:10,730
President!

80
00:06:10,730 --> 00:06:12,570
President!

81
00:06:13,380 --> 00:06:16,280
Although you're the president, I think

82
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:18,550
that opening someone else's doors so abruptly is going a bit far.

83
00:06:18,550 --> 00:06:21,710
Sorry, there was just some rumor I heard.

84
00:06:21,710 --> 00:06:24,440
I've become too sensitive.

85
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:28,900
Do you sleep in the study?

86
00:06:30,230 --> 00:06:33,220
Ah, yes. Sometimes, I sleep in here after working.

87
00:06:33,220 --> 00:06:36,250
I see. Then let's talk here.

88
00:06:36,250 --> 00:06:38,370
You sit too, Director Cha.

89
00:06:39,810 --> 00:06:41,450
Yes.

90
00:06:45,210 --> 00:06:48,940
I heard something strange about you today, Director Cha.

91
00:06:48,940 --> 00:06:50,290
About me?

92
00:06:50,290 --> 00:06:52,540
I heard that you were living with a female employee in your department.

93
00:06:52,540 --> 00:06:54,850
Is that true?

94
00:06:55,910 --> 00:06:57,780
Moreover, that female employee is

95
00:06:57,780 --> 00:07:01,090
the janitor that you got onto the team a month ago,

96
00:07:01,090 --> 00:07:04,000
through your connection or something.

97
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:07,780
The second-hand embarrassment was such that I yelled at the gossip-monger.

98
00:07:07,780 --> 00:07:09,990
You are not that kind of person, Director Cha.

99
00:07:09,990 --> 00:07:12,670
Someone who can't draw the line between public and private matters,

100
00:07:12,670 --> 00:07:16,400
and making arbitrary hiring decisions, all blinded by your desire for a woman.

101
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:18,090
You're not someone who would do that.

102
00:07:18,090 --> 00:07:19,880
I already told you before, but

103
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:21,990
Go Bok Sil has got what it takes to become a great merchandising director, so

104
00:07:21,990 --> 00:07:23,770
I merely gave her an opportunity.

105
00:07:23,770 --> 00:07:26,360
She didn't waste that opportunity, but secured a contract employee position.

106
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:28,700
From there all is the result of her own hard work.

107
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:30,810
So please don't disparage by saying

108
00:07:30,810 --> 00:07:33,440
it was because of my desire or personal feelings.

109
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:36,360
Of course not! If I can't trust

110
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:38,580
Director Cha, who under the sun can I trust?

111
00:07:38,580 --> 00:07:41,570
What I'm saying is, there isn't anything good that will come out of it

112
00:07:41,570 --> 00:07:43,530
if that kind of rumor is circulating.

113
00:07:43,530 --> 00:07:46,870
Getting a scratch on your clean and pure reputation,

114
00:07:46,870 --> 00:07:50,270
I don't like that.

115
00:07:50,270 --> 00:07:53,370
Thank you for your concern.

116
00:07:54,470 --> 00:07:57,730
That employee... Go Bok Sil.

117
00:07:57,730 --> 00:08:01,840
What do you think of sending her to the Shanghai branch?

118
00:08:03,630 --> 00:08:05,290
Excuse me?

119
00:08:06,110 --> 00:08:08,450
Think about it.

120
00:08:08,450 --> 00:08:12,940
It might be a good opportunity for her, too.

121
00:08:15,470 --> 00:08:18,390
Sorry for coming at such a late hour.

122
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:20,590
No need to see me out.

123
00:08:20,590 --> 00:08:22,220
Have a safe trip back.

124
00:08:49,790 --> 00:08:52,760
Director, I'm sorry.

125
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:54,790
We only thought of ourselves.

126
00:08:54,790 --> 00:08:57,840
I didn't know it would affect you like this.

127
00:08:57,840 --> 00:09:00,130
If Bok Sil is sorry,

128
00:09:00,130 --> 00:09:02,330
I'm sorry as well.

129
00:09:02,330 --> 00:09:04,340
Go pack your belongings.

130
00:09:05,990 --> 00:09:08,020
Halt.

131
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:11,610
I don't know who's been saying such nonsense,

132
00:09:11,610 --> 00:09:13,270
but I'm fine with it.

133
00:09:13,270 --> 00:09:15,550
I'm okay with you guys living here.

134
00:09:15,550 --> 00:09:18,810
The house owner says it's okay so stop overreacting. It's late

135
00:09:18,810 --> 00:09:21,210
so just go sleep.

136
00:09:25,980 --> 00:09:29,000
Director, but I don't want to put you in a tough spot because of us—

137
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:32,440
Thank you for taking care of us even when it's tough on you.

138
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:34,980
Hey, what are you doing?

139
00:09:34,980 --> 00:09:39,260
It's basic manners to happily accept someone's kind gestures.

140
00:09:39,260 --> 00:09:40,790
Right, Director?

141
00:09:40,790 --> 00:09:43,960
What's with you? You're actually saying something right.

142
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:46,580
But, Director.

143
00:09:46,580 --> 00:09:49,850
You don't by any chance like Bok Sil, do you?

144
00:09:49,850 --> 00:09:51,170
Stop saying nonsense!

145
00:09:51,170 --> 00:09:54,300
What? Your president said so earlier.

146
00:09:54,990 --> 00:09:56,840
You don't like her, right?

147
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:23,300
- Of course not.
- What a relief.

148
00:10:24,710 --> 00:10:30,370
Then, will you really send Bok Sil to the Shanghai branch?

149
00:10:30,910 --> 00:10:32,510
No.

150
00:10:33,060 --> 00:10:35,880
Give up the useless worrying and go to sleep.

151
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:37,670
Go upstairs!

152
00:10:38,150 --> 00:10:41,840
If you're in an awkward situation at work, should I spread the rumor that I live together (with you) too?

153
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:44,390
Just hurry upstairs!

154
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:51,700
If we send Go Bok Sil to Shanghai, Louis has to follow her.

155
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:56,430
Louis just needs to stay out of sight until the company shares are taken care of.

156
00:10:56,430 --> 00:10:59,650
Louis doesn't even have any form of identification. How do we send him to China?

157
00:10:59,650 --> 00:11:02,840
I'll take care of that.

158
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,710
Go Bok Sil wouldn't want to go, either.

159
00:11:04,710 --> 00:11:06,880
She's looking for her brother as if her life's on the line.

160
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:09,650
But isn't her brother already dead?

161
00:11:10,150 --> 00:11:14,170
Ma Ri, you need to tell her that truth.

162
00:11:14,690 --> 00:11:18,960
She might want to go off somewhere far away if she finds out her brother died.

163
00:11:19,510 --> 00:11:23,430
That is a perfect motivating force to send someone far away.

164
00:11:24,060 --> 00:11:25,990
Don't waste time.

165
00:11:33,190 --> 00:11:36,060
Are you sure this person bought flowers here?

166
00:11:36,060 --> 00:11:39,420
Yes, he was so picky picking the rose...

167
00:11:39,420 --> 00:11:41,720
So which one did he pick?

168
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:43,800
An orange rose.

169
00:11:48,540 --> 00:11:51,820
Butler Kim, do you know the language of flowers well?

170
00:11:51,820 --> 00:11:54,510
Red means passion, yellow means jealousy,

171
00:11:54,510 --> 00:11:56,430
and pink means happiness.

172
00:11:56,430 --> 00:11:58,740
Do you know what orange means?

173
00:11:58,740 --> 00:12:00,430
I'm not sure.

174
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:02,710
First love.

175
00:12:03,790 --> 00:12:06,650
Have you even been in love, Butler Kim?

176
00:12:07,710 --> 00:12:11,510
Young Master, such things shouldn't be asked so directly.

177
00:12:11,510 --> 00:12:13,830
It's rude.

178
00:12:14,410 --> 00:12:17,400
Why get hung up on such things between us?

179
00:12:20,620 --> 00:12:23,680
Will I ever fall in love, too, some day?

180
00:12:24,220 --> 00:12:26,130
Who knows.

181
00:12:27,140 --> 00:12:32,580
If I find someone I love, I'm going to give this orange rose.

182
00:12:32,580 --> 00:12:34,990
Just one stem.

183
00:12:40,020 --> 00:12:41,400
What's with your expression?

184
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:43,630
It's Young Master for sure.

185
00:12:43,630 --> 00:12:45,800
Did he say anything else?

186
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,470
He was going to give the flower to the woman he lives with.

187
00:12:48,470 --> 00:12:49,590
Sorry?

188
00:12:49,590 --> 00:12:53,840
They didn't seem married. Maybe they just live together?

189
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,100
How can a cohabiting guy be...

190
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:58,920
He paid for the flower with six 500 won coins, so I remember him even more.

191
00:12:58,920 --> 00:13:02,620
Considering the payment method, there is no way he's the young master.

192
00:13:02,620 --> 00:13:03,930
- Thank you.
- Sure.

193
00:13:03,930 --> 00:13:06,310
I'm certain, I'm certain, I'm certain.

194
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:12,190
A thousand won for one! Two thousand won for two! Take your pick!

195
00:13:12,190 --> 00:13:13,910
Louis.

196
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:22,040
Hyung, how's this?

197
00:13:23,770 --> 00:13:25,620
You really have a great fashion sense!

198
00:13:25,620 --> 00:13:29,230
I'm asking because I'm really curious, but did this kid talk to you, this time, too?

199
00:13:29,230 --> 00:13:31,090
- Yeah.
- What did it say?

200
00:13:31,090 --> 00:13:34,010
"Louis. Louis." It calls my name.

201
00:13:34,010 --> 00:13:38,810
Louis, Louis, no matter how I look at you, you sure seem out of your mind.

202
00:13:38,810 --> 00:13:42,190
You have a long way to go to reach my level.

203
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:47,570
Here's the money.

204
00:13:50,100 --> 00:13:51,030
Come again.

205
00:13:51,030 --> 00:13:53,690
- Can I have a bag?
- Sure, sure.

206
00:13:53,690 --> 00:13:55,840
Thank you for the bag.

207
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:57,890
Yes, come again.

208
00:13:58,290 --> 00:13:59,940
Hyung, did they say the culprit isn't caught yet?

209
00:13:59,940 --> 00:14:01,050
Right.

210
00:14:01,050 --> 00:14:04,310
That's weird. I gave them a big hint, so it's about time he got caught.

211
00:14:04,310 --> 00:14:08,480
You know, I wrote a letter to the UN not too long ago. Our country will be reunified soon. Just wait and see.

212
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:09,560
What are you talking about?

213
00:14:09,560 --> 00:14:13,160
It's dumbfounding, right? The same goes for you.

214
00:14:17,810 --> 00:14:20,110
Okay, got it.

215
00:14:20,110 --> 00:14:23,380
Team Leader! We found out suspect Jung Gil Do's residence.

216
00:14:23,380 --> 00:14:25,460
Good, let's roll out.

217
00:14:25,460 --> 00:14:28,360
We don't know which way he may try to elude us, so keep a tight watch around his house.

218
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:30,340
- Yes, Sir.
- Let's go.

219
00:14:30,340 --> 00:14:32,500
What are you busy packing for?

220
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:34,780
You better move it! Aren't you listening?

221
00:14:37,550 --> 00:14:39,300
Bok Sil.

222
00:14:40,270 --> 00:14:41,310
Yes, Team Leader.

223
00:14:41,310 --> 00:14:43,520
Talk with me after work.

224
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:45,170
Okay.

225
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:52,120
What is going on with the list of the vendors who are going to participate in the Korea Black Friday event?

226
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:54,010
Is it going well under every category?

227
00:14:54,010 --> 00:14:57,490
Of course. There are many vendors and products hoping to participate.

228
00:14:57,490 --> 00:14:59,460
As you can see, just the number of sample goods is staggering.

229
00:14:59,460 --> 00:15:01,950
That is an eyesore. Organize them now!

230
00:15:01,950 --> 00:15:03,490
Yes, Sir.

231
00:15:03,490 --> 00:15:05,880
Manager Lee, what about the temporary part-time worker I asked you to hire?

232
00:15:05,880 --> 00:15:07,750
He will come today.

233
00:15:07,750 --> 00:15:09,230
Bok Sil went to get him.

234
00:15:09,230 --> 00:15:11,050
Is that so?

235
00:15:15,870 --> 00:15:17,140
Why are you alone?

236
00:15:17,140 --> 00:15:19,820
The part timer had something urgent come up.

237
00:15:19,820 --> 00:15:21,290
He says he's sorry for not coming.

238
00:15:21,290 --> 00:15:24,530
- What?!
- As expected, your talent for hiring help is outstanding as well.

239
00:15:24,530 --> 00:15:26,920
How can you be so outstanding in all facets?!

240
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:28,770
- I can again—
- Forget it!

241
00:15:28,770 --> 00:15:30,340
Yes, Sir...

242
00:15:31,770 --> 00:15:34,090
I'll look into it.

243
00:15:41,150 --> 00:15:43,130
Move them, move them.

244
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:48,190
I said I'm sure. He's our regular here.

245
00:15:48,190 --> 00:15:53,060
He always pays with 500 won coins, so I can't help but remember him.

246
00:15:54,220 --> 00:15:57,500
Is he a panhandler?

247
00:15:57,500 --> 00:16:01,500
He keeps on using only coins that he begged for.

248
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:06,340
He just bought a sweatshirt here, so I put a comment at the social networking site.

249
00:16:06,890 --> 00:16:08,790
Did you say just now? When?

250
00:16:08,790 --> 00:16:11,580
Maybe... 20 minutes ago?

251
00:16:11,580 --> 00:16:12,490
Twenty minutes?!

252
00:16:12,490 --> 00:16:14,210
- Yes.
- Oh!

253
00:16:14,210 --> 00:16:17,610
If that regular comes again, please give me a call. Please.

254
00:16:17,610 --> 00:16:19,380
Please!

255
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:34,150
- Mackerel.
- Come on!

256
00:16:38,020 --> 00:16:40,370
Hey, let's go over there.

257
00:16:41,090 --> 00:16:43,220
- Are you all right?
