00:19:05,290 --> 00:19:07,540
- Hello.
- Hello.

292
00:19:07,540 --> 00:19:09,310
Hello.

293
00:19:10,230 --> 00:19:13,260
Did Director Cha Joong Won go somewhere?

294
00:19:13,260 --> 00:19:16,430
He's at lunch right now.

295
00:19:16,430 --> 00:19:18,170
What about Go Bok Sil?

296
00:19:18,590 --> 00:19:21,700
- You know Bok Sil as well?
- Yes, we're close.

297
00:19:22,540 --> 00:19:25,230
Don't tell me they went to eat together?

298
00:19:25,230 --> 00:19:28,100
I'm not... sure about that.

299
00:19:28,670 --> 00:19:30,490
How annoying.

300
00:19:30,950 --> 00:19:32,900
Please give me a cup of Maxim Gold.

301
00:19:32,900 --> 00:19:34,550
Sure.

302
00:19:39,210 --> 00:19:40,300
Who is he?

303
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:43,510
I saw that guy somewhere...

304
00:19:43,510 --> 00:19:46,550
Those clothes, shoes and scarf are all Director's.

305
00:19:46,550 --> 00:19:48,240
Huh?

306
00:19:50,250 --> 00:19:52,760
Director, you have a guest.

307
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:09,300
Are you crazy? Who said you could wear my clothes? Do you want to die?

308
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:20,950
He's the part-timer, who will take care of our miscellaneous work.

309
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:22,810
Say hello.

310
00:20:22,810 --> 00:20:24,600
Hello.

311
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:26,100
- His name is...
- Louis.

312
00:20:26,100 --> 00:20:28,610
Louis the 14th, that Louis?

313
00:20:28,610 --> 00:20:31,290
No last name? Just Louis?

314
00:20:37,180 --> 00:20:38,800
Wang. (Wang means king in Korean)

315
00:20:40,600 --> 00:20:42,110
Wang Louis.

316
00:20:48,640 --> 00:20:50,100
Bok Sil?

317
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:51,640
Oh... Sunbaenim.

318
00:20:51,640 --> 00:20:52,680
Who?

319
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:53,920
I'm her guardian.

320
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:59,180
That's right! He's Bok Sil's boyfriend. Isn't that right, Wang Louis?

321
00:20:59,180 --> 00:21:00,900
No, no! No!

322
00:21:00,900 --> 00:21:03,320
I'm more than her boyfriend. Umm,

323
00:21:03,320 --> 00:21:05,160
Together, we just live—

324
00:21:05,830 --> 00:21:10,990
Are finding someone. He's helping me find my brother.

325
00:21:10,990 --> 00:21:14,640
Then why are you wearing Director's clothes?

326
00:21:18,320 --> 00:21:20,450
Oh, we live...

327
00:21:22,030 --> 00:21:24,710
We met trying to lose weight.

328
00:21:24,710 --> 00:21:26,940
You lost a lot of weight.

329
00:21:26,940 --> 00:21:31,090
What are you doing not getting to work?! There are mountains of stuff piled up in front of the storage room!

330
00:21:31,090 --> 00:21:32,150
I got it!

331
00:21:32,150 --> 00:21:34,540
What the?

332
00:21:36,730 --> 00:21:38,560
Here you go.

333
00:21:39,420 --> 00:21:42,490
Thank you. Your name?

334
00:21:42,490 --> 00:21:43,910
Oh.

335
00:21:48,810 --> 00:21:52,950
Lee Kyung Gook. I'll remember that name.

336
00:21:52,950 --> 00:21:54,510
Yes.

337
00:21:59,880 --> 00:22:01,240
Huh.

338
00:22:02,050 --> 00:22:04,030
- He's the part timer.
- Ah...

339
00:22:06,310 --> 00:22:11,280
You served coffee to a part timer. Nice one, Manager!

340
00:22:18,950 --> 00:22:23,540
How did you meet Bok Sil? How did you come here? Do you have a job?

341
00:22:23,540 --> 00:22:25,030
Where does the director go to work out?

342
00:22:25,030 --> 00:22:28,160
Stop paying attention to the part timer and get to work!

343
00:22:28,160 --> 00:22:32,100
Chief Lee, what are you doing?!

344
00:22:41,650 --> 00:22:45,040
First open the boxes and check the contents. Then sort them by categories like clothes, baby goods,

345
00:22:45,040 --> 00:22:48,770
cosmetics, household items etc., and take them to each person in charge.

346
00:22:48,770 --> 00:22:51,150
Looks like there's nothing much to it.

347
00:23:11,620 --> 00:23:12,890
Can I just leave them here?

348
00:23:12,890 --> 00:23:14,640
Yes.

349
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:23,490
Oh my!

350
00:23:39,620 --> 00:23:42,830
Dad! Dad! Big trouble!

351
00:23:42,830 --> 00:23:44,130
Ma Ri.

352
00:23:44,130 --> 00:23:47,080
Miss, what is the matter?

353
00:23:48,220 --> 00:23:49,920
Hello.

354
00:23:49,920 --> 00:23:52,750
Director Joo, let's talk later.

355
00:23:52,750 --> 00:23:54,420
Oh, yes.

356
00:24:01,290 --> 00:24:05,740
Dad! Dad! Louis came to the company!

357
00:24:05,740 --> 00:24:07,580
He's in the product planning department right now!

358
00:24:07,580 --> 00:24:11,770
What? Why did he suddenly appear at the product planning department?

359
00:24:11,770 --> 00:24:13,950
Did you find out what he's there for?

360
00:24:13,950 --> 00:24:18,700
I didn't have time, I came running here after being surprised.

361
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:23,060
Wait. Maybe he came as a part timer?

362
00:24:23,060 --> 00:24:24,340
Part timer?

363
00:24:24,340 --> 00:24:29,400
We had too much work because of the Black Friday event, so we decided to get a part timer today.

364
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:34,300
Because Go Bok Sil is working here, Louis keeps getting mixed up in this.

365
00:24:34,300 --> 00:24:37,840
We need to take care of Go Bok Sil quickly.

366
00:24:41,280 --> 00:24:42,200
What do we do?

367
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:44,420
No return address...?!

368
00:24:45,220 --> 00:24:47,380
Oh no! What's going on here?

369
00:24:47,380 --> 00:24:49,960
L-Louis, Wang Louis, are you okay?

370
00:24:49,960 --> 00:24:53,860
Oh my!

371
00:24:53,860 --> 00:24:55,830
Are you okay?

372
00:24:56,580 --> 00:24:59,530
Oh no! What should we do?

373
00:24:59,530 --> 00:25:01,930
Of course I'm not okay.

374
00:25:01,930 --> 00:25:04,980
I'm positive some woman terrorized me just now.

375
00:25:08,460 --> 00:25:10,790
She's not here.

376
00:25:11,540 --> 00:25:17,230
That woman pushed these boxes on me as soon as she saw me.

377
00:25:17,230 --> 00:25:21,170
If it's not Assistant Manager Kwon or Hye Joo, then...

378
00:25:21,170 --> 00:25:22,260
Team Leader Baek?

379
00:25:22,260 --> 00:25:26,410
- What nonsense.
- What do you take the Wanna-be-Star of Goldline for?

380
00:25:27,150 --> 00:25:29,990
I know I saw her somewhere.

381
00:25:35,240 --> 00:25:36,560
Oh my!

382
00:25:36,560 --> 00:25:41,250
That's right! She's the woman who crashed into me with her car.

383
00:25:43,340 --> 00:25:46,730
That woman hit me with her car,

384
00:25:46,730 --> 00:25:50,360
paid me, and even called me.

385
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:54,480
So, the woman that pushed the boxes on you

386
00:25:54,480 --> 00:25:58,560
is the same woman that hit you with her car?

387
00:26:06,100 --> 00:26:07,760
Here, get up.

388
00:26:09,590 --> 00:26:11,530
He looks normal, but he's a bit weird.

389
00:26:11,530 --> 00:26:14,110
- He has a delusional disorder.
- Yeah.

390
00:26:14,110 --> 00:26:18,860
I was envious of Bok Sil because of her handsome boyfriend, but he turns out to be a sour apricot that's only good to look at.

391
00:26:18,860 --> 00:26:21,590
But he seems so familiar.

392
00:26:21,590 --> 00:26:24,540
Wang Louis. Did I see him somewhere?

393
00:26:24,540 --> 00:26:26,430
You saw me somewhere?

394
00:26:26,430 --> 00:26:29,060
Where? When? Huh?

395
00:26:29,830 --> 00:26:31,040
Look. Hurry.

396
00:26:31,040 --> 00:26:32,850
Why hurr--

397
00:26:32,850 --> 00:26:35,710
- But what's this smell?
- What is this salty smell?

398
00:26:35,710 --> 00:26:38,930
Oh my!

399
00:26:38,930 --> 00:26:41,210
- Hobo?!
- Pervert!

400
00:26:41,210 --> 00:26:42,630
Whoa! What the!

401
00:26:42,630 --> 00:26:45,760
- Ouch!
- What are you? A beggar or what?

402
00:26:48,230 --> 00:26:49,800
Oh my, unbelievable!

403
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:54,620
Then they met at the lobby when Bok Sil worked as a janitor?

404
00:26:54,620 --> 00:26:58,600
A fateful meeting of a country chicken janitor and a homeless person suffering from a delusional disorder?

405
00:26:58,600 --> 00:27:01,980
Wow, what a tearjerking story. This is so sad.

406
00:27:14,330 --> 00:27:16,040
What should she do?

407
00:27:19,230 --> 00:27:20,950
Here.

408
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:27,810
Hey, what happened?

409
00:27:27,810 --> 00:27:30,940
Bok Sil, I got hit here.

410
00:27:30,940 --> 00:27:33,390
By whom?

411
00:27:33,390 --> 00:27:35,030
By this.

412
00:27:36,440 --> 00:27:40,070
Geez, you should've been more careful.

413
00:27:40,070 --> 00:27:42,650
Looks like it hurts.

414
00:27:42,650 --> 00:27:45,130
Bok Sil, Isn't it strange?

415
00:27:45,980 --> 00:27:49,360
You're the only one who believes me.

416
00:27:49,360 --> 00:27:53,160
Director always tells me that I boast.

417
00:27:56,320 --> 00:28:02,330
You only need one person who believes in you in life.

418
00:28:03,530 --> 00:28:05,590
And that one person is Bok Sil?

419
00:28:05,590 --> 00:28:08,070
Why are you asking, of course.

420
00:28:16,450 --> 00:28:21,770
Team Leader Baek, did you ever hit Wang Louis with your car by chance?

421
00:28:24,150 --> 00:28:27,400
What are you talking about?

422
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:29,390
Who's Wang Louis?

423
00:28:29,390 --> 00:28:32,360
You haven't seen the new part timer?

424
00:28:32,360 --> 00:28:34,600
N-No, I haven't.

425
00:28:34,600 --> 00:28:38,840
As expected! He is a strange person.

426
00:28:38,840 --> 00:28:42,280
Hye Joo said that he's Bok Sil's boyfriend.

427
00:28:42,280 --> 00:28:44,150
Does Bok Sil care only about the looks?

428
00:28:44,150 --> 00:28:46,310
You mean she is a lover of human kind.

429
00:28:49,120 --> 00:28:51,990
We will be off to a business meeting.

430
00:28:51,990 --> 00:28:53,780
Okay.

431
00:29:19,490 --> 00:29:20,690
Here.

432
00:29:23,770 --> 00:29:26,350
What are you doing here, not going in?

433
00:29:27,940 --> 00:29:31,140
Are you trying to avoid someone?

434
00:29:31,140 --> 00:29:34,420
No.

435
00:29:45,250 --> 00:29:46,820
The suspect is caught. Let's go to the police station!

436
00:29:46,820 --> 00:29:48,470
He's caught? Let's go!

437
00:29:48,470 --> 00:29:51,060
Let's all go. Quickly!

438
00:29:51,060 --> 00:29:53,340
- Hurry, hurry!
- Did the culprit get caught?

439
00:29:53,340 --> 00:29:55,720
Yes, yes, he is caught.

440
00:29:56,500 --> 00:29:59,720
That's weird. I gave them a big hint, so it's about time he got caught.

441
00:29:59,720 --> 00:30:03,240
Wow, he needs to become a fortune teller.

442
00:30:03,240 --> 00:30:04,890
Hella goosebumps.

443
00:30:04,890 --> 00:30:07,670
Jung Gil Do, who is the suspect for the Eunsung-dong serial murder case,

444
00:30:07,670 --> 00:30:09,830
was apprehended.

445
00:30:09,830 --> 00:30:14,780
He had left no evidence at the previous crime scenes, but he failed to see the unidentified powder

446
00:30:14,780 --> 00:30:17,140
that was spilled on the floor of the third crime scene.

447
00:30:17,140 --> 00:30:19,930
Bok Sil is such a neat girl. Why was her floor in that state at the time?

448
00:30:19,930 --> 00:30:22,040
His footprints that he never dreamed of leaving...

449
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:23,990
Who in the world do you think had done it?

450
00:30:24,590 --> 00:30:26,870
Day of the incident

451
00:30:38,550 --> 00:30:43,590
When is Bok Sil coming? Did something happen?

452
00:31:16,040 --> 00:31:18,340
I can't pick it up.

453
00:31:27,180 --> 00:31:30,210
Sheesh, seriously.

454
00:31:56,130 --> 00:31:59,220
It's so difficult to drink coffee.

455
00:32:01,190 --> 00:32:05,090
I should just wait for Bok Sil.

456
00:32:20,730 --> 00:32:22,780
Five minutes before the incident occurs.

457
00:32:48,780 --> 00:32:52,180
What is this?

458
00:33:18,180 --> 00:33:23,970
Team leader, shouldn't we give Louis a reward?

459
00:33:23,970 --> 00:33:26,230
It's not even information about the suspect, man.

460
00:33:26,230 --> 00:33:30,990
But still, he gave us information about the foot print, that wasn't even in our database, that sped up the process of finding the suspect.

461
00:33:30,990 --> 00:33:34,590
I approve. If we hadn't investigated that store that sells those cycling shoes,

462
00:33:34,590 --> 00:33:36,860
- we wouldn't have found the culprit.
- Jeez, you!

463
00:33:36,860 --> 00:33:38,850
Wow, he might really hit us.

464
00:33:38,850 --> 00:33:44,310
Then find out if we can give him part of it rather than 100% of the reward.

465
00:33:44,310 --> 00:33:47,380
Take down the police line as soon as you're done analyzing the scene.

466
00:33:47,380 --> 00:33:48,790
Yes!

467
00:33:48,790 --> 00:33:51,600
Is the victim in the hospital still unconscious?

468
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:53,810
Yes. There's a good possibility that it was a mugger.

469
00:33:53,810 --> 00:33:55,820
Should I keep investigating in that direction as well?

470
00:33:55,820 --> 00:33:57,220
We should do that.

471
00:33:57,220 --> 00:34:01,550
How many times did I tell you that it was an incorrect comment?

472
00:34:01,550 --> 00:34:04,550
I mistook him for someone else.

473
00:34:04,550 --> 00:34:07,770
That's why I erased the comment.

474
00:34:07,770 --> 00:34:10,000
Please verify it one more time.

475
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:12,620
I'm busy, so I'll be going now.

476
00:34:13,660 --> 00:34:15,970
But please...

477
00:34:15,970 --> 00:34:18,360
You're no longer accepting tips? Why are you suddenly doing that?

478
00:34:18,360 --> 00:34:21,260
- We were contacted by the Pain Patch Man's guardian.
- His guardian?

479
00:34:21,260 --> 00:34:23,890
He said his son was mentally deficient, so he was going around doing weird things.

480
00:34:23,890 --> 00:34:26,340
He didn't want that kind of son being on television.

481
00:34:26,340 --> 00:34:30,730
From a parent's point of view, it's quite understandable. We took down all the videos and photographs.

482
00:34:30,730 --> 00:34:33,040
That man is definitely someone I know.

483
00:34:33,040 --> 00:34:36,680
That's enough. He said his parents have now come forward.

484
00:34:36,680 --> 00:34:40,590
I'm sure that he is someone who really resembles the dead Young Master Louis.

485
00:34:40,590 --> 00:34:43,370
And how could a dead person be running around?

486
00:34:43,370 --> 00:34:45,050
Would it be possible to get his contact information?

487
00:34:45,050 --> 00:34:47,330
We don't really know that either. Good-bye, then.

488
00:34:47,330 --> 00:34:49,220
Excuse me.

489
00:34:52,250 --> 00:34:57,930
President Baek, we went around to the hospital and the broadcasting station.

490
00:34:57,930 --> 00:35:01,430
That man is not Young Master Louis.

491
00:35:01,430 --> 00:35:03,470
Yes, I understand.

492
00:35:03,470 --> 00:35:06,030
Who are you talking to?

493
00:35:17,040 --> 00:35:20,630
I thought you said you hated the sight of me? Why did you change your mind?

494
00:35:20,630 --> 00:35:22,050
How is Mother?

495
00:35:22,050 --> 00:35:25,350
Mother? She's sleeping. Why do you ask?

496
00:35:25,350 --> 00:35:28,460
Escort Mother and come to Seoul.

497
00:35:28,460 --> 00:35:30,930
By chance...

498
00:35:30,930 --> 00:35:32,900
Did you find Louis?

499
00:35:32,900 --> 00:35:36,860
No. No, I said no!

500
00:35:37,940 --> 00:35:41,870
Don't say anything strange to Mother, and just escort her here.

501
00:35:41,870 --> 00:35:46,420
If you say something pointless again, I'm not going to let it go.

502
00:35:52,160 --> 00:35:55,380
Who have you been talking to non-stop since morning?

503
00:35:56,810 --> 00:35:59,210
It's just a friend I know.

504
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:03,350
You're lying right now.

505
00:36:03,350 --> 00:36:06,720
I'll ask you again. Do you have someone you need to report to?

506
00:36:06,720 --> 00:36:12,320
What does it matter who I talk to?! Why are you telling me what to do?! You're being ridiculous, seriously!

507
00:36:15,610 --> 00:36:17,900
Why is she lying to me?

508
00:36:17,900 --> 00:36:21,230
No way. Is she talking to her boyfriend?

509
00:36:21,230 --> 00:36:23,700
Sheesh, just what am I thinking?

510
00:36:23,700 --> 00:36:25,890
Wait for me!

511
00:36:26,830 --> 00:36:29,540
Ah, the pasta at that place is really delicious!

512
00:36:29,540 --> 00:36:34,470
I was so happy we had pasta, but now I'm sad I have to stay and work overtime.

513
00:36:34,470 --> 00:36:37,410
Does Team Leader Baek have a lot to do outside the office? She's been keeping out of sight all day long.

514
